Got the results of my arthogram today (pictured above is my hand after the procedure). I was told I have a few tears in my muscles and ulnar impingement syndrome causing a disabling pseudoarhtrosis.

I'm getting sent to a specialist and I hope all I need is some kind of physical therapy, but surgery isnt ruled out. 
Either way, looks like my brace will be a part of my outfit now! I will not stop being a #DJ or #beatmaker / #producer . I may have to do a lot of adjustments but I will not let this stop me from pursuing my passions in #creating and performing, and being a #musicmaker.

My first year of skateboarding has passed. And was it a doozy!

First I want to thank everyone at @thelocalskateshop.com_ . You're all kind and awesome people. Most of all, Thank you for welcoming me into the skate community!

Speaking of community, I got to meet and befriend so many great people in this city.

In my first year of skating I broke two bones in my right arm skating Beaz for the very first time, from learning how to ollie to 50-50 grinds, I think for a 30 something year old skater I got to develop some neat tricks. But only thanks to being around some awesome skaters! 
It was a wild ride for my first year and I hope for many more in the future. #iloveskateboarding
